<section xml:id="sec-set-operations">
    <title>Set operations</title>
    
    <p>
        Given two (or more) sets. There are various operations we can perform with them.
        Sometimes it is useful to think of the sets, say <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> as living
        within some larger <q>univsersal set</q>, <m>U</m>. 
        That is there is a set <m>U</m> where <m>A \subseteq U</m> and <m>B \subseteq U</m>.
    </p>

    <p>
        The first set operations we will consider are the <term>union</term> 
        and <term>intersection</term>of two sets.
    </p>

    <definition xml:id="def-union">
        <title>Union of sets</title>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Let <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> be sets. The <term>union</term> of <m>A</m> and <m>B</m>
                is the set whose elements are the elements of <m>A</m> <em>or</em> <m>B</m>.
                We denote this as
                <me>
                    A \cup B = \{x \mid x \in A \vee x \in B\}.
                </me>
            </p>
            
        </statement>
    </definition>

    <definition xml:id="def-intersection">
        <title>Intersection of sets</title>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Let <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> be sets. The <term>intersection</term> of <m>A</m> and <m>B</m>
                is the set whose elements are the elements of <m>A</m> <em>and</em> <m>B</m>.
                We denote this as
            <me>
                A \cup B = \{x \mid x \in A \wedge x \in B\}.
            </me>                
            </p>
        </statement>
    </definition>

    <p>
        We can visualize the union and intersection of two sets using Venn diagrams:
    </p>

    <figure>
    <caption>The union of two sets</caption>
    <image width="60%">
        <prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org" label="prefigure-union">
            <diagram dimensions="(300,180)" margins="5">
            <coordinates bbox="(0,0,10,6)">
                <define-shapes>
                <circle at="A" center="(4,3)" radius="2"/>
                <circle at="B" center="(6,3)" radius="2"/>
                </define-shapes>

                <shape shapes="A,B" operation="union"
                fill="blue" stroke="black"/>
                <shape shape="A" stroke="black"/>
                <shape shape="B" stroke="black"/>
                <rectangle lower-left="(0,0)" dimensions="(10,6)" stroke="black"/>

                <label anchor="(2,3)" alignment="nw"><m>A</m></label>
                <label anchor="(8,3)" alignment="ne"><m>B</m></label>
                <label anchor="(5,0.5)"><m>A\cup B</m></label>
            </coordinates>
            </diagram>
        </prefigure>
    </image>
    </figure>

    <figure>
    <caption>The intersection of two sets</caption>
    <image width="60%">
        <prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org" label="prefigure-intersection">
            <diagram dimensions="(300,180)" margins="5">
            <coordinates bbox="(0,0,10,6)">
                <define-shapes>
                <circle at="A" center="(4,3)" radius="2"/>
                <circle at="B" center="(6,3)" radius="2"/>
                </define-shapes>

                <shape shapes="A,B" operation="intersection"
                fill="blue" stroke="black"/>
                <shape shape="A" stroke="black"/>
                <shape shape="B" stroke="black"/>
                <rectangle lower-left="(0,0)" dimensions="(10,6)" stroke="black"/>

                <label anchor="(2,3)" alignment="nw"><m>A</m></label>
                <label anchor="(8,3)" alignment="ne"><m>B</m></label>
                <label anchor="(5,0.5)"><m>A\cap B</m></label>
            </coordinates>
            </diagram>
        </prefigure>
    </image>
    </figure>
    
</section>